<HEADLINE>   Primakov Undergoes Successful Gallstone Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Russian Foreign Minister Yevgeny
Primakov had an operation today to remove gallstones, reports said.
</P>
<P>
The one-hour operation at Moscow's Central Clinical Hospital at
4.30 p.m. Moscow time (13:30 GMT), went well and there were no
complications, the Itar-Tass news agency said.
</P>
<P>
"The condition of Yevgeny Primakov after surgery is good, there
are no complications," the Itar-Tass quoted an official as saying
at the hospital.
</P>
<P>
Primakov, 67, was hospitalized earlier today. 
</P>
