<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russian Official Stresses Relations With China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Russian Deputy Foreign Minister
Grigory Karasin said developing Sino-Russian relations was a top
priority in Russia's foreign policy, the Itar-Tass news agency
reported today.
</P>
<P>
The minister, speaking ahead of Chinese President Jiang Zemin's
visit to Russia from April 22 to 26, said the visit was a "very
important event" in Russian-Chinese relations.
</P>
<P>
The two sides are expected to sign a joint declaration.
</P>
<P>
Karasin dismissed as nonsense, statements by some politicians
that Russia was developing relations with China because it was not
"getting on well with" NATO.
</P>
<P>
He said the two countries were developing an equal partnership
aimed towards strategic cooperation in the 21st century. He said
they were upgrading confidence-building measures.
</P>
<P>
Karasin said that Russian Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin
may visit China in late May and early June . 
</P>
</TEXT>
