<HEADLINE> Tisco Is Among The Best in Thailand, Says IBCA </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 18 (Xinhua) -- IBCA, the European credit rating
agency, today published a detailed survey of the credit-worthiness
of seventeen of the largest Thai finance companies, undertaken in
February 1997.
</P>
<P>
The agency found that the best ranking companies were Tisco
(affiliated to Bankers Trust), National (Siam Commercial Bank),
Dhana Siam (Siam Commercial Bank) and Phatra (Thai Farmers Bank).
</P>
<P>
It said, this group generally adopted conservative accounting
policies, exhibited high levels of capital and liquidity, and
adopted less aggressive growth strategies in recent years.
</P>
<P>
They maintain relatively sound asset quality and appear to be
adequately provided against loan losses, the agency added.
</P>
<P>
Those ranked lowest on the survey list were International Trust
and Finance, General Finance, CMIC, Siam City Credit and Wall
Street Finance.
</P>
<P>
They exhibited weaknesses in several areas, including low
capital, a high level of accrued interest, low profitability (and
in some cases disguised losses), extremely low liquidity, and
evidence of deteriorating asset quality, the agency said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
