<HEADLINE> Switzerland to Aid Tanzania's Malaria project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Switzerland will provide
one billion Tanzania Shillings (about 1.6 million US Dollars) for
research in insecticide treated nets for malaria control in the
Kilombero Valley, Morogoro Region, about 300 kilometers west of
Dar es Salaam.
</P>
<P>
According to a statement issued here today by the Swiss
Embassy, the agreement was signed here on Thursday by the Swiss
Ambassador to the country, Lise Favre and the Principal Secretary
in the Ministry of Finance, Peter Ngumbulu.
</P>
<P>
