<HEADLINE> Removal of Lesotho PM as Party Leader Declared </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 18 (Xinhua) -- The removal of Lesotho's
Prime Minister Ntsu Mokhehle as the leader of the ruling
Basotholand Congress Party (BCP) was declared null and void today
in Maseru, capital of the land-locked kingdom.
</P>
<P>
Mokhehle's application for a court order to set aside his
removal was upheld by Justice Winston Churchill Maqutu in the
Lesoth Hight Court#,reported the South African Press Association.
</P>
<P>
Mokhehle was sacked as the BCP leader by the BCP's annual
conference held in Maseru on February 28 because he was
reportedly accused of failing to perform his duties effectively
and efficiently.
</P>
<P>
Maqutu said Mokhehle's term of office will expire in January
next year under the party's constitution. Therefore, he would
remain as interim leader until a new leader was elected at the
BCP's next annual conference.
</P>
<P>
He also ordered the BCP's National Executive Committee to
hold a party conference within three and half months to elect a
new leader.
</P>
<P>
Maqutu said the committee has failed to provide advance
notification of at least one month that there would be a motion
for the leader's removal according to the BCP constitution.
</P>
