<HEADLINE> China Must become "One of Pillars of World Trade System": WTO Director-General </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 19 (Xinhua) -- China must become one of the
pillars of the world trade system, since it has already been an
important member of a global economy marked by mutual-dependence,
Renato Ruggiero, director-general of the World Trade Organization
(WTO) said here today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a symposium on the WTO and China's service trade,
he noted that the WTO increasingly needs China to be an active
member of the organization, in order to make it a real global
trade system which can shoulder heavy responsibilities in the 21st
century.
</P>
<P>
The negotiations for China's joining the WTO have entered the
last phase, he said, adding that the country's inclusion into the
organization as soon as possible will inject a new vigor to a
stable multilateral global trade system.
</P>
<P>
About 200 people from the relevant Chinese sectors attended the
symposium. 
