<HEADLINE> Mauritian Prime Minister Ends China Trip </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Mauritian Prime Minister Navin
Ramgoolam ended a visit to China and left here today by a special
plane.
</P>
<P>
Ramgoolam, who flew here from Hangzhou Thursday afternoon, met
with Guangdong Provincial Governor Lu Ruihua and discussed ways to
increase economic and trade cooperation between Mauritius and the
province.
</P>
<P>
During Ramgoolam's stay here, he also visited the 81st
Guangzhou Export Commodities Trade Fair and the Guangdong Folk Art
Gallery.  
</P>
