<HEADLINE> 40 PLA Advance Personnel To Arrive in HK Monday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Forty advance personnel of the
People's Liberation Army (PLA), led by Major General Zhou Borong,
will arrive in Hong Kong at 1:00 pm April 21 via the Lok Ma Chau
Crossing, a Hong Kong government spokesman said today.
</P>
<P>
"The PLA advance personnel will be in uniform but will not
carry arms. The eight vehicles brought in by them will carry Hong
Kong number plates," he said.
</P>
<P>
"At the border, the party will go through immigration and
customs clearance and declare articles imported in line with
normal procedures," he added.
</P>
<P>
After that, the party will proceed straight to the Prince of
Wales Barracks where they will be greeted by Major General Bryan
Dutton, commander of the British Forces in the territory, the
spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this week, the Chinese and British sides on the
Sino-British Joint Liaison Group (JLG) reached agreement over the
first batch of the PLA advance personnel.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, 40 advance personnel, led by a deputy
commander of the future PLA Garrison in Hong Kong, who is an
officer of the rank of Major General, will arrive in Hong Kong in
late April.
</P>
<P>
They will make practical preparations for the PLA to take over
the responsibility for the defense of Hong Kong after midnight
June 30, including familiarization with the military sites,
liaison with the British Forces and the Hong Kong government, and
coordination of communications support. 
</P>
</TEXT>
