<HEADLINE> 700 Million Yuan Goes to Mountainous Areas Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUIYANG, April 19 (Xinhua) -- China will spend 700 million yuan
in preferential loans on land improvement, river harnessing,
planting trees, building roads, and electricity supply in
mountainous areas this year.
</P>
<P>
According to a national meeting on comprehensive development of
mountainous areas and poverty relief through forestry, the country
will increase the number of pilot counties in development of
mountainous areas to 59 in 30 province-level areas.
</P>
<P>
The 58 million people living under the poverty line are
concentrated in mountainous areas.
</P>
<P>
The country has decided to allow individuals to develop barren
mountains and allow the transfer of barren mountain-use rights,
according to State Councillor Chen Junsheng.
</P>
<P>
Chen said at the meeting that flexible policies will be granted
to newly-opened land.
</P>
<P>
A total of 15.3 billion yuan will be spend on the country's
help-the-poor projects this year, 45 billion more than that in
1996.  
</P>
</TEXT>
