<HEADLINE> American Takes Lead in Philippine Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGUIO CITY, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Kevin Wentworth of the United
States shot his second 62 in two days Saturday and leaped into a
four-stroke lead with a 13-under-par 191 going into the final
round of the Philippine Open.
</P>
<P>
Fellow American Larry Barber, who led by one shot after
Friday's second round, carded a 1-under-par 67 and slipped to
second place at 195.
</P>
<P>
Wentworth, No. 8 on the Asian Tour Order of Merit, fired eight
birdies over the 5,252-yard Club John Hay Golf Course in the
northern city of Baguio.
</P>
<P>
Filipino Willy de Tomas was in third place, one shot behind
Barber at 196 after firing a 66.
</P>
<P>
Behind him were four players at 197, Australia Stephen Leaney,
Robert Jan Derksen of the Netherlands, current Asian Tour leader
Edward Fryatt of England, and American Steve Haskins. 
</P>
</TEXT>
