<HEADLINE> Iran Denies Involvement in Dhahran Bomb Blast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 19 (Xinhua) -- A senior Iranian military officer
today denied any link between his forces and a Saudi national
suspected of involvement in the last June bombing of U.S. Air
Force dormitory that killed 19 American servicemen in Dhahran,
Saudi Arabia
</P>
<P>
Major General Mohsen Rezaei, Commander of the Islamic
Revolution's Guards Corps (IRGC), rejected the accusation made
by the Washington Post Weekly.
</P>
<P>
The weekly alleged last week that a high ranking IRGC
official had been linked to Hani Abd Arahim al Zayegh who
was arrested in Canada last month for his alleged role in
the June 25 bombing.
</P>
<P>
"This is not the first time that America embarks on
telling lies about the Islamic Republic of Iran," said the
general.
</P>
<P>
Usually, he added, after such an incident, American and
Israeli officials and media try to hold Iran responsible without
producing any evidence.
</P>
<P>
Saudi Arabia has reportedly obtained information on the
anti-U.S. bombing but refused to divulge any details before the
investigation is complete.
</P>
<P>
The United States accused Iran of involvement in the
bombing and warned that American forces would launch a military
strike if Iran is found responsible. 
</P>
</TEXT>
