<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kenya's Josephat Ndeti Wins Belgrade Marathon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Kenya made a clean 1-2-3 sweep
in the 10th Belgrade Marathon on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The 23-year-old Josephat Ndeti chalked up the title in two
hours 13 minutes and 37 seconds, followed by his fellow countrymen
Reuben Chebutich and Onesmus Mutisya.
</P>
<P>
Chebutich finished second in 2:13:44 while Mutisya took third
with a time of 2:14:02.
</P>
<P>
Ahmed Salah of Djibouti, 39, Last year's winner here and still
the third fastest in history, gave up in the second half of the
race because of a leg injury.
</P>
<P>
Irina Bogacheva from Kyrgyzstan, who came in second in the Los
Angeles race in February, was the fastest woman by clocking
2:34:56.
</P>
<P>
Behind her by 1:49 minutes was Russia's Jelena Makolova. The
third position went to Adriana Barbu from Romania, who finished in
2:38:18.
</P>
<P>
About 500 runners from 26 countries attempted the full marathon
of 42.195 kilometers while 2,600 others participated in the
half-marathon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
