of opinions and views and the enhancement of trust and
understanding among the countries in the Asia-Pacific region. This
is not only good for maintaining peace and stability in the
region, but also for building a peaceful, stable, ever-growing,
and prosperous world in the 21st century, he said.
</P>
<P>
Den Hideo from Japan said that the meeting is of great
significance because it provides an opportunity of exchange among
people from different geographical locations, nationalities, and
countries in the region.  
