<HEADLINE> Iranian Women Advised Not to Marry Foreigners </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Iranian authorities warned its
female citizens not to marry foreigners in view of a lot of
troubles in the future, a press report said here today.
</P>
<P>
Qolam Reza Husseinpour, director in charge of foreign
nationals of the Khorassan province, has openly called on the
female in the country to "avoid marriage with foreign nationals
without legal registration."
</P>
<P>
The Persian daily Akhbar quoted the official as saying the
marriage of some Iranian females in the northeastern province
with Afghan nationals has created a lot of problems and
complications.
</P>
<P>
The children of such marriages lack any legal identities and
a number of Iranian women are living in chaos and confusion with
their children after they lose their spouses for various reasons.
</P>
<P>
The provincial official said a recent national census showed
that some Iranian women were married to immigrants from Iraq,
Afghanistan, Pakistan and Bangladesh.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, there are 400,000 Afghan immigrants
presently staying in various parts of the province either legally
or illegally.
</P>
<P>
Among the marriages with foreigners involved, he noted, some
30,000 marriages lacked any official registration at notary
offices.
</P>
<P>
Most of the problems come when foreigners such as Afghan
nationals suddenly disappear and abandon their Iranian wives and
their families.
</P>
<P>
In general, Iran does not encourage Iranians, females in
particular, to get married to foreigners, while males' marriage
of this kind is more tolerable, because theoretically they can
bring women back from other countries and increase the Muslim
populace.
</P>
<P>
But, some young girls, especially those who know foreign
languages, reportedly have the intention of marrying Americans
and Europeans. 
</P>
</TEXT>
