<HEADLINE> Training Course on Cave Technology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUIYANG, April 19 (Xinhua) -- An international training course
on cave technology will be held this July in southwest China's
Guizhou province, famous for its unique karst cave landscape.
</P>
<P>
The 20-day course, jointly sponsored by French and Chinese
interests, will be given to some 40 research personnel and
spelunkers from nearly ten countries.
</P>
<P>
The course will cover scientific knowledge on karst topography,
and protection measures in caves. Field research will also be
conducted.
</P>
<P>
China's southwest region, as one of the world's largest karst
landscapes, has attracted scientific exploring teams from more
than ten countries since 1980s. At present, China only has 20
personnel engaged in cave research. 
</P>
