<HEADLINE> Pankratov Crashes Again At Short-couse Swimming </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GOTHENBURG, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Double Olympic champion Denis
Pankratov got another heavy blow at the World Short-course
Swimming Championships as he failed to make his second final here
on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The Russian, who holds all the men's short-course and
long-course butterfly world marks, led the first 50 meters of his
200 butterfly heat but then lost his momentum. He could not
survive the challengge from defending champion Scott Goodman of
Australia and Germany's Thomas Rupprath, finishing a disappointing
ninth place, just out of evening's finals.
</P>
<P>
The world number one male butterfier clocked one minute 58.22
seconds, more than five seconds shy of the 1:52.64 world mark he
set in Gelsenkirchen, Germany in February.
</P>
<P>
Pankratov did not manage a place in the 100 butterfly final on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
American Misty Hyman showed her perfect underwater technique
and came close to the world record in the women's 100 butterfly
heats. She touched the pad in a championship record of 58.32.
</P>
<P>
Hyman set a world mark of 58.29 last December but that was
bettered to 58.24 on March 28 by Japan's teenager Olympian Ayari
Aoyama.
</P>
<P>
American Jenny Thompson, with a 100 freestyle gold and 50
freestyle silver already in her pocket, was second-fastest overall
in 58.67.
</P>
<P>
Claudia Poll, who broke her own 200 freestyle world mark on
Friday, faces a serious challenge from 15-year-old Australian
Natasha Bowron in the final of the women's 400 freestyle.
</P>
<P>
Bowron, gold medallist in Friday's 800 freestyle, led
qualifiers in four minutes 8.72 seconds, beating Poll into the
second at 4:08.93.
</P>
<P>
Venezuela's Francisco Sanchez led qualifiers in the men's 100
freestyle with a time of 47.85.
</P>
<P>
Defending champion Fernando Scherer of Brazil failed to
qualify, finishing 17th overall in 49.57.
</P>
<P>
South Africa's Joanne Russell led the women's 100 breaststroke
qualifiers in 1:08.14 and Russia's Andrei Korneev topped the men's
200 breaststroke qualifiers in 2:09.82. 
</P>
</TEXT>
