<HEADLINE> Krajicek, Roux Vie For Japan Open Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Top seed Richard Krajicek will
clash with Lionel Roux for the men's singles title at the Japan
Open tennis tournment after they beat their respective rivals on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Krajicek, overcoming Patrick Rafter's dramatic play with a big
serve and booming returns, outplayed his Austrlian opponent 7-6
(7-5), 6-3 in one hour 16 minutes.
</P>
<P>
There were only two break points during the match. The 1996
Wimbledon champion Krajicek, who is seeking his second title of
this year, saved the one in the sixth game, and capitalized on the
one against Rafter, 24, in the second set's eighth game. He also
served eight aces.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, No. 16 seed Roux upset fifth seed Thomas Johansson
of Sweden 4-6, 7-5, 6-3 in a marathon semi-final match which
lasted two hours 15 minutes, reaching only the second final of his
career.
</P>
<P>
The 86th-ranked Roux, who beat injured No. 2 seed Boris Becker
in the third round, also reached his only other final in Japan in
Osaka in 1994. 
</P>
