<HEADLINE> Japanese Takes 500cc Pole Position In Japan GP </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Japan's Tadayuki Okada earned his
second pole position of the season on Saturday to take the yellow
jersey for Sunday's Japanese 500 cc Grand Prix in Suzuka.
</P>
<P>
Okada, riding on a Honda, clocked two minutes 7.952 seconds
during the second qualifying practice session at the
5.864-kilometer Suzuka circuit, reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
Okada was just 0.065 seconds ahead of team mate and world
champion Michael Doohan, while Spain's Alex Criville came in third.
</P>
<P>
Doohan, who took the provisional pole on Friday by clocking two
minutes 12.908 seconds in the rain, was quoted as saying that he
was not so concerned about finishing second.
</P>
<P>
Japan's Tetsuya Harada clinched the pole position for the 250cc
race, while Japans Noboru Ueda will start in front for the 125cc
race. 
</P>
