<HEADLINE> Congo National Assembly President Visits Guizhou </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUIYANG, April 19 (Xinhua) -- President of the National
Assembly of the Congo Andre Milongo and his party left southwest
China's Guizhou Province for Shenzhen after a three-day visit.
</P>
<P>
Milongo said that he is glad to be the first African parliament
leader to visit the province.
</P>
<P>
Welcoming the Congolese visitors, Wang Chaowen, chairman of the
Standing Committee of the Guizhou Provincial People's Congress,
briefed the visitors on conditions of the province, Guizhou's
social and economic achievements in the past few years, and the
regional autonomy of ethnic minorities.
</P>
<P>
Wang, who is also chairman of the Nationalities Affairs
Committee of China's National People's Congress (NPC), said that
Guizhou and the Congo share many similarities, hoping that the two
sides can increase exchanges to seek common development.
</P>
<P>
Noting that his country has an over two million population
belonging to over 70 nationalities, Milongo said that Guizhou's
harmonious co-existence of various ethnic groups and social
stability left a deep impression on him and his party.
</P>
<P>
He went on to say that China's policy on national unity and the
successful resolution to its national problems set a good example
for Africa to follow in achieving national reconciliation.
</P>
<P>
The delegation from the Congo also visited some rural areas and
scenic spots during their visit in Guizhou.
</P>
<P>
Milongo and his party were invited by the NPC Standing
Committee. 
</P>
