<HEADLINE> NPC Chairman Meets Benin National Assembly Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Qiao Shi, chairman of the
Standing Committee of China's National People's Congress (NPC),
met here this afternoon with a delegation from the National
Assembly of Benin led by its president Bruno Amoussou.
</P>
<P>
They pledged to further increase exchanges and cooperation
between the NPC and the Benin National Assembly.
</P>
<P>
Extending a welcome to the delegation, Qiao said that China and
Benin enjoy good relations, and there have been many exchanges
between the two parliaments.
</P>
<P>
The two countries have supported and helped each other in
various fields such as politics, economy and culture, he added.
</P>
<P>
"China hopes that Benin will embark on the road of economic
prosperity," he said.
</P>
<P>
Briefing the delegation on China's economic development, Qiao
said that in the past two decades, guided by Deng Xiaoping's
theory on building socialism with Chinese characteristics, China
has been pursued the reform and opening-up policy, scoring
tremendous economic achievements.
</P>
<P>
However, Qiao said that China is still encountering many
difficulties, and China's modernization still requires efforts of
several generations.
</P>
<P>
He said that China needs a long-term peaceful and stable
international situation, and it has all along been against
hegemonism and power politics and followed an independent foreign
policy of peace.
</P>
<P>
China pays close attention to the political and economic
stability for its over 1.2 billion population, he said, pointing
out that economic development can not be promoted unless a
peaceful international environment and a stable domestic situation
are achieved.
</P>
<P>
Amoussou said that Benin and China have a long history of
friendship, and that his country is satisfied with the development
of bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
He added that the development of bilateral friendship manifests
the mutual support and help among developing countries.
</P>
<P>
He said that Benin witnessed China's rapid development by its
own efforts and its great progress in developing the economy and
building the new society.
</P>
<P>
Amoussou noted that Benin people pay close attention to China's
achievements.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the development of China is not only the
development of the world force for peace, but also a necessary
condition for world peace.
</P>
<P>
The delegation is here as guests of the NPC Standing Committee.
</P>
