<HEADLINE> Plane Crash Kills 17 People in Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Seventeen people were killed
today when a plane of Merpati airline of Indonesia crashed near
Bandara Tanjung Pandan, Belitung island, a flight officer said
here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The MZ-106 plane with 48 people on board, which took off from
Soekorno-Hatta airport, Jakarta, at 6:32 a.m., crashed at 7:30
a.m. local time in an area, two kilometers from Bandara Tanjung
Pandan, flight officer Iman Pramugari Karma Tiningsih said.
</P>
<P>
Till 11:20 a.m., 17 people had died, he said.
</P>
<P>
According to witnesses, the crash took place in the sky over
the village of Cacang Butor.
</P>
<P>
Efforts are continuing to find out victims of the accident as
the airline authorities estimated that there are some people could
be saved, he added.
</P>
<P>
A team of doctors has arrived in the area where the plane
crashed. But the reason of the crash has not been found, he said.
</P>
<P>
Minister of Communication Haryanto Dhanutirto has left Jakarta
to the scene of the accident, he disclosed. 
</P>
