<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nigeria to Close Failed Community Banks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 19 (Xinhua) -- The Central Bank of Nigeria is working
out modalities on how to close down the distressed community banks
that failed to recapitalize as the government requires, the New
Nigerian reported today.
</P>
<P>
According to Central Bank statistics, there are more than 1,000
community banks in the country and about 90 percent of them are
distressed.
</P>
<P>
The paid-up capital requiremenet of community banking has remained
250,000 naila (nearly 3,000 U.S. Dollars currently) since its
establishment in 1988, compared with 500 million naira (about 5.9
million dollars) for commercial and merchant banks.
</P>
<P>
The capital base of community banks has almost been eroded by
inflation over the years and can no longer withstand the inflationary
pressure, according to Central Bank Governor Paul Ogwuma.
</P>
<P>
The Nigerian government has earlier this year announced all
distressed commercial and merchant banks should increase their paid-up
capital to the 500 million naila level before the end of March,
otherwise they will be liquidated.
</P>
<P>
The new capital requirement has not been announced publicly for
community banks, which are licensed with the aim of providing
assistance to people of the grassroots as well as encouraging banking
habit among the people.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970419.0100 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guineaworm Scourge Spreads in Northeast Nigerian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 19 (Xinhua) -- The outbreak of guineaworm has now
reached an alarming level and aroused serious concern from the people
of Gombe State in northeastern Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
The cases of the desease were put at 593 as at last month in all
the 11 local government areas of the state, one of Nigeria's six
created late last year, the New Nigerian reported today.
</P>
<P>
A total of 42 villages and three local government areas in the
state have been marked of guineaworm endemic areas, the government
daily said.
</P>
<P>
In Jore Village, one of the endemic areas, an estimated 70 percent
of th adult population was infected by the disease, with some of them
completely incapacitated by the scourge.
</P>
<P>
The report said some civil servants described the situation as a
disaster, blaming the government for its negative attitude towards
checking the menace.
</P>
<P>
But Gombe State Commissioner for Health Jalo Daudu said that a
task force committee on guineaworm eradication has been set up to
check the menace.
</P>
<P>
As soon as the committee completes its report on effective
eradication, the government will swing into action, he said.
</P>
<P>
He also appealed to the federal government and other
non-governmental organizations for aid.  
</P>
</TEXT>
