<HEADLINE> Nigeria Plans First Disneyland in Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria is planning to build a
Disneyland in its capital Abuja, the Guardian reported today.
</P>
<P>
The report said the first Disneyland in Africa will occupy an
area of 300 acres on the shore of the River Gurara and cost about
70 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
It will house a vast array of amusement facilities such as
challenging nides, spectacular stage shows, wild animal habitation and
water-based leisure activities.
</P>
<P>
It will also accommodate an international hotel, night clubs,
casino, sports center and cultural galleries.
</P>
<P>
The complex, to be known as National Recreation Center, will be the
first major tourism investment project in Nigeria in recent years, the
newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
Its sponsor, the Federal Capital Territory Development Authority
has expressed the wish to enter into partnership with foreign
investors on the project.
</P>
<P>
The authority emphasized that the investment into the project will
be protected by the Nigerian government under an investment protection
agreement.  
</P>
