<HEADLINE> Russia Offers to Upgrade T-72 Tanks Supplied to India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Russia has offered to modernize
India's T-72 tanks by supplying a comprehensive active tank
defense system, Press Trust of India (PTI) reported today.
</P>
<P>
Quoting a highly placed Russian official, the report said the
new system called "Arena", which would be mounted on the tanks
sold by Russia before, is capable of providing a high degree of
protection to tanks from anti-tank grenades, self-guided and
unguided missiles, all kinds of shells fired by infantry as well
as those launched from helicopters.
</P>
<P>
According to Russian military experts, the "Arena" can make
India's T-72 tanks, estimated to be around 1,400-1,700, almost
invulnerable to guided or unguided anti-tank weapons.
</P>
<P>
"Arena" was created for the Russian T-80 tanks at the end of
1980s and is currently exported by the Russian arms trading
corporation "Roosvooruzhenie".  
</P>
</TEXT>
