<HEADLINE> Shipbuilding Export up in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai, China's leading
industrial center, will produce about 900,000 dead weight tons of
ships this year, 97 percent of which is expected to be sold
abroad, according to the Shanghai Shipbuilding Corporation.
</P>
<P>
China ranks third in the world in the capacity of shipbuilding
after Japan and the Republic of Korea.
</P>
<P>
Statistics have shown that the output value of the shipbuilding
industry in Shanghai exceeded five billion yuan (602 million US
dollars) annually.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai boasts 12 institutes and colleges featuring the
shipbuilding industry and a number of large shipyards including
Jiangnan and Hudong shipyards, which can produce ships of 10,000
tons.  
</P>
