<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-Premier Meets Egyptian Prime Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Zhu Rongji
met here today with visiting Egyptian Prime Minister Kamal Ahmed
El-Ganzouri, and had a cordial conversation with him.
</P>
<P>
Extending a welcome to Ganzouri, Zhu said he is glad to meet
his old friend again in Beijing and recalled his visit to Egypt
three years ago as guest of Ganzouri.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said that China attaches great importance to Ganzouri's
current visit, which is manifested by his fruitful meetings and
talks with Chinese leaders including President Jiang Zemin,
Premier Li Peng, and Chairman of the National Committee of the
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference Li Ruihuan, as
well as the several agreements on bilateral cooperation signed
during this visit.
</P>
<P>
Zhu voiced his conviction that this visit will promote the
further development of Sino-Egyptian friendship and cooperation
for the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Ganzouri said that the close contacts between leaders of the
two countries play an important role in strengthening bilateral
friendly ties.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the Egyptian government pays much attention to
this visit, and he is satisfied with its result, adding that it is
conducive to the continuous development of bilateral friendship
and cooperation, especially bilateral economic and trade relations.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said that both China and Egypt are developing countries,
and China has all along paid attention to strengthening relations
with developing countries. "This is a basic point for China's
foreign policy," he emphasized.
</P>
<P>
Pointing out that bilateral economic and trade relations are an
important component of the friendly relations between the two
sides, Zhu said that the Chinese side is glad to see that
Sino-Egyptian economic and trade relations have had a sustained
and steady development in the past years under the joint efforts
from both sides.
</P>
<P>
He noted that both sides are exploring new means and forms for
expanding bilateral economic and trade cooperation. He is
confident that on the basis of a deepening mutual understanding,
bilateral reciprocal cooperation will be continuously expanded, he
said.
</P>
<P>
This morning, Ganzouri met with Chinese Minister in charge of
the State Planning Commission Chen Jinhua.  
</P>
