set deficit to oust American Kimberly Po, securing her spot in the
women's final of the Japan Open here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Sugiyama, top player in Japan after Kimiko Date retired last
year, beat Po 5-7, 6-4, 6-1 for a clash against American Amy
Frazier.
</P>
<P>
