take on Sugiyama in the final.
</P>
<P>
Sugiyama, seeded fourth, saved two set points at 4-5 and one
more at 5-6 before losing the first set to second seed Po.
</P>
<P>
She rallied back from 40-0 to break Po's third game of the
second set with five straight points and broke again in the
seventh.
</P>
<P>
Being broken in the eighth, she had to save one break point to
serve out the set.
</P>
<P>
In the decider, Sugiyama, who lost two previous matches against
Po, surged to a 4-1 and rebounded from 0-40 to hold her serve for
5-1 before sealing the one hour 50 minutes competition. 
