<HEADLINE> China Develops New Flight Vehicle For Water Transportation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, April 19 (Xinhua) -- China has developed a new kind of
flying machine that is a hybrid of helicopter and hovercraft.
</P>
<P>
The flying boat was co-developed by the Beihai Township
Enterprises' Inviting Outside Investment Center and the Beihai
Dayang Flying Boat Corporation Ltd. in Beihai, southwest China's
Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
The craft, about to take test flights here, will be used as a new
means of marine transportation. Designed on the basis of a sea
plane and hovercraft, it can take off and land on water surface
and flies just 0.5 to 2 meters above it.
</P>
<P>
With a flight speed of 90-200 km per hour, it boasts such
advantages as smooth, stealthy flight, and it does not need an
airport or wharf.
</P>
<P>
It is predicted that the craft will be used widely in marine
transportation, patrol, and anti-smuggling efforts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
