<HEADLINE> Regional Peace, Disarmament, Symbiosis Conference Opens In Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 19 (Xinhua) -- The Third Conference on Peace,
Disarmament and Symbiosis in Asia-Pacific opened here today.
</P>
<P>
The theme of the non-governmental regional forum is peace,
development and promotion of understandings among countries in
the region. The current session of the forum is jointly-sponsored
by the Chinese Association for International Understanding (CAIU)
and relevant organizations from Japan and the Philippines.
</P>
<P>
Some 80 renowned personages, scholars and experts from 10
countries attend the meeting.
</P>
<P>
They will exchange views on the topics of peace, security,
disarmament, economic cooperation and sustainable development.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese People's
Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC) Wan Guoquan made a
speech at the opening ceremony of the meeting this morning.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Asia-Pacific region is an area with rapid
economic growth in the world. It is of great significance that
countries in the region further expand non-governmental contacts
to exchange views on economic and political issues of common
concern.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Chairwoman of the Standing Committee of China's National
People's Congress (NPC) Lei Jieqiong also attended the opening
ceremony.
</P>
<P>
The first and second conferences were held respectively in
Tokyo in 1992 and Manila in 1994. 
</P>
</TEXT>
