<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka to Benefit from SAPTA Second Round Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka is seeking to benefit
from the second round of trade negotiations of the South Asian
Association for Regional Cooperation (SAARC) Preferential Trading
Arrangement (SAPTA), official sources here said today.
</P>
<P>
SAARC, founded in December 1985, groups Bangladesh, Bhutan,
India, the Maldives, Nepal, Pakistan and Sri Lanka.
</P>
<P>
The exemption reached by the second round of trade negotiations
of the SAPTA is to be implemented from June 1.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lanka has listed 92 items for tariff concessions in the
second round of trade negotiations on tariff barriers between
members states, while the first round offered 67 items.
</P>
<P>
It is anticipated that in the entire region of SAARC, as many
as 2,000 items will eventually come under the SAPTA agreement.
</P>
<P>
The sources assured that Sri Lankan consumers and manufacturers
will stand to benefit from the SAPTA agreement.
</P>
<P>
They pointed out that it is the best time for Sri Lanka to
expand its markets in the region as Sri Lanka has got a very good
reputation for the quality of its goods and the skills of its
workforce.
</P>
<P>
The SAPTA is also expected to provide opportunities for joint
ventures or direct import of components from other SAARC countries
for manufacturing processes, the sources added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
