<HEADLINE> Alba Marks European Independence: Prodi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, April 18 (Xinhua) -- The mission in Albania, codenamed
Operations Alba (Dawn), shows that dawn has come for the European
countries to cast aside the shadow of the United States, and
commit themselves to the European affairs directly, Italian Prime
Minister Romano Prodi said today.
</P>
<P>
Prodi said Operation Alba signals a brand new start for Italy
and Europe as a whole to shoulder the responsibility of solving
European problems -- without following their powerful ally across
the Atlantic.
</P>
<P>
He was speaking in the northeastern city of Trieste.
</P>
<P>
Operation Alba is headed by the Organization of Security and
Cooperation in Europe (OSCE), with the European Union (EU)
providing humanitarian aid supplies, and a multinational force
guaranteeing the security of the aid delivery.
</P>
<P>
In operations so far, the Italian-led 6,000-strong
multinational force had been sent to the chaotic Balkan country to
secure road and ports for aid delivery.
</P>
<P>
The force comprises troops from seven other countries, France,
Spain, Greece, Romania, Turkey, Denmark and Austria.
</P>
<P>
The participation of countries from the Baltic Sea to the
Mediterranean indicated that European nations had all explicitly
realized their duties within the region, Prodi said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
