<HEADLINE> Lower Price Rise in Guangdong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Price rises in Guangdong, an
economic star in south China, slowed down with each passing
month in the first quarter of this year.
</P>
<P>
The growth rate of the retail price index has declined from 2.5
percent in January to 0.2 percent in March, the lowest since June
1991.
</P>
<P>
The rise in the price of daily-use consumption goods decreased
from January's six percent to two percent last month.
</P>
<P>
In the first quarter, the prices of foodstuffs and durable
industrial goods remained stable.
</P>
<P>
