<HEADLINE> Thai Furniture Exports to Grow 4.6 percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Thai furniture exports are
expected to reach 18.2 billion baht (728 million U.S. dollars)
this year, up 4.6 percent from last year, the Thai Commerce
Ministry predicts.
</P>
<P>
However, the department of business economics under the
ministry said Thai furniture exports this year will face fiercer
competition from other countries like China, Indonesia, India and
Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
Thai furniture exports were valued at 17.41 billion baht (696.4
million dollars) last year, edging up only 0.1 percent from 1995
due to the sluggish world market, rising labor costs and a
shortage of raw materials.
</P>
<P>
Japan was the largest importer of Thai furniture last year,
taking up 47.5 percent of the total, followed by the United States
with 18.6 percent, the European Union with 12.5 percent, South
Korea with 1.9 percent.  
</P>
