<HEADLINE> China's Light Industry Output Grows </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 19 (Xinhua) -- China's output of light industry
enjoyed a year-on-year growth of 12 percent in the first two
months of this year, according to latest statistics from the China
National Council of Light Industry.
</P>
<P>
The growth was 0.6 percentage points higher than the nation's
overall industrial growth and was one percentage point higher than
the heavy industrial growth, today's China Daily noted.
</P>
<P>
The sector completed output of 316 billion yuan-worth during
the period, said the paper, adding that the output of 14 out of 24
major products increased compared with the same months of 1996,
while that of other ten products dropped.
</P>
<P>
Electric cookers, whose output is 30 percent more than during
the same period last year, showed the largest growth.
</P>
<P>
Following it were dairy products, soft drinks, washing machines,
sugar and refrigerators.
</P>
<P>
The daily said that the growth was instigated by the brisk
consumer market during the Spring Festival, which fell in February
this year.
</P>
<P>
The nation's retail sales increased 16 per cent in the
January-February period reaching 450.2 billion yuan, and sales by
the light industry topped 392.7 billion yuan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
