<HEADLINE> Thai Souvenir Exports Expected to Recover </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's exports of gifts,
souvenirs and decorative items are expected to hit 31.87 billion
baht (1.27 billion U.S. dollars) in value this year, up about 0.5
percent from last year.
</P>
<P>
The increase is foreseen as the major markets in the United
States and Europe are expected to boom this year, according to the
Thai Commerce Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Thailand earned 31.6 billion baht (1.26 billion dollars) from
exports of these products last year, down 5.1 percent from 1995,
said the export promotion department under the ministry.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. was the largest importer of the Thai products last
year, taking in 41.1 percent of the total, or 13 billion baht (520
million dollars), followed by Japan with 12.7 percent, and Germany
with 6.8 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
