<HEADLINE> Voelker Disqualified in 100m Backstroke </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Second finisher Lu Donghua of
China was promoted to the top place in the 100 meters backstroke
as Sandra Voelker of German was disqualified at the World
Short-Course Championships in Gothenburg, Sweden, on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The German, who had earlier won the 50 meters freestyle gold,
led throughout the backstroke and touched home first, 0.25 seconds
ahead of Lu, the fastest qualifier.
</P>
<P>
But officials disqualified her for swimming under water more
than the 15 meters allowed after the start.
</P>
<P>
The decision gave China a one-two, with Lu first in 59.75
seconds and Chen Yan second in one minute 0.14 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Defending champion Misty Hyman, third in Thursday's 200
butterfly took the bronze in 1:00.17. 
</P>
