<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Taiwan-Funded Enterprises Booming in Xiamen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Taiwan's business people have
invested more than three billion US dollars since 1984 in Xiamen,
a coastal city close to the island, in east China's Fujian
Province.
</P>
<P>
The number of Taiwan-funded projects reached 1,382 at the end
of February this year, contributing to nearly half of Xiamen's
total industrial value, statistics show.
</P>
<P>
The coverage of the enterprises has been expanded to the
sectors with high technical content, such as electronics,
chemicals, machinery, building materials, and medicines, from
earlier labor-intensive industries such as the making of shoes and
umbrellas.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the average investment on the
Taiwan-funded projects has increased to more than 2.2 million US
dollars from less than one million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
More than 50 enterprises registered an investment of more than
ten million US dollars. Fifteen of the largest 100 companies in
Taiwan have poured investment into Xiamen. 
</P>
</TEXT>
