<HEADLINE> Spaniards Make Clean Sweep of Last Four Spots </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Four Spaniards marched along in a
quene for the semifinals of the Barcelona Open tennis tournament
by downing their quarterfinal opponents respectively on Friday.
</P>
<P>
This would be the first time for the locals to complete the
last four spots in a world-class tennis tournament.
</P>
<P>
Carlos Moya, Albert Costa, Alberto Berasategui and Alberto
Portas make the semi-finals all-Spaniard affairs.
</P>
<P>
Moya had his best tennis of the week, taking only 65 minutes to
beat Andrei Medvedev of Ukraine 6-4, 6-2, and seventh seed Costa
put an end to Frenchman Cedric Pioline's run in a rain-soaked
battle, winning 6-4, 6-2.
</P>
<P>
Berasategui, the ninth seed, ousted Brazilian Fernando Meligeni
6-2, 7-5, and Portas defeated Morocco's Karim Alami 6-2, 7-5.
</P>
<P>
On Saturday, Costa will play his close friend Moya, with Portas
facing Berasategui in the semifinals. 
</P>
