<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ukraine, Uzbekistan to Cooperate on Energy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Ukraine and Uzbekistan have agreed
to promote energy cooperation, the Ukrainian-Uzbek Joint Committee
announced here today.
</P>
<P>
The two countries, before July 1, will sign an agreement which
will allow Uzbekistan to sell Ukraine natural gas from 1997 to
2005, said the committee.
</P>
<P>
The joint committee closed its first session today as Uzbek
Prime Minister Utkur Sultanov ended his two-day visit to Kiev.
</P>
<P>
The committee also discussed the possibility to transport
Turkmen oil to Ukraine through Uzbek territories.
</P>
<P>
Turkmenistan will become an important oil source for Ukraine
when Ukraine begins to seek other energy partners rather than
Russia. At present, about 70 percent of Ukraine's energy is
imported from Russia, which has been considered an obstacle to
Ukraine's economic development.
</P>
<P>
Ukraine and Uzbekistan have also agreed on an oil-for-medical
equipment deal. This provides for Ukraine to send to Uzbekistan
medical equipment worth 30 million dollars in exchange for
Uzbekistan diesel fuel. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
