<HEADLINE> U.S. Secretary of State to Visit Guatemala </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, April 18 (Xinhua) -- United States Secretary of
State Madeleine Albright will visit Guatemala on May 4 to
familiarize herself with the peace process in the Central American
country.
</P>
<P>
Guatemalan Foreign Minister Eduardo Stein said in Guatemala
City that in her one-day visit, Albright will learn about the
advances in the peace, disarmament and demobilization processes of
the former Guatemalan guerrillas.
</P>
<P>
The Guatemalan minister said the agenda for Albright's trip "is
very simple," because her visit only focuses on knowing directly
the advances in the implementation of the peace agreements.
</P>
<P>
United States President Bill Clinton will visit Costa Rica on
May 8, where he will meet with the Central American presidents to
discuss relations between the U.S. and the Central American
countries.
</P>
<P>
Stein declined to reveal whether Albright will discuss the
summit between Central American presidents and Clinton, and
migration problems. 
</P>
</TEXT>
