<HEADLINE> Voelker Wins Women's 50 Freestyle Gold </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Sandra Voelker of Germany won
the title of the women's 50 meters freestyle event on the second
day of the World Short-Course Championships in Gothenburg, Sweden,
on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Voelker, who took the silver behind Jenny Thompson in
Thursday's 100 freestyle, beating the American into second place
by 0.08 of a second in 24.70 seconds.
</P>
<P>
China's world record holder Le Jingyi, who had to settle for
third in the 100m, won the bronze again in 24.83.
</P>
<P>
Le, gold medalist in the event at the Atlanta Olympic Games
last summer, had won both the 50 and 100 freestyle at each of the
two previous World Short-Course Championships. 
