<HEADLINE> Australians Break Freestyle Relay Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, April 18 (Xinhua) -- The Australians set another
world record by winning the 800-meter men's freestyle relay in the
World Swimming Short Course Championships in Gothenburg, Sweden on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Their winning time of 7:02.74 smashed a record of 7:05.17 that
had stood since 1986 when it was set by West Germany.
</P>
<P>
The Australian team consisted of Michael Klim, Grant Hackett,
William Kirby and Matthew Dunn.
</P>
<P>
On Thursday, another Australian foursome swam home the gold in
a world record timing of 3:30.66 in the men's 4x100 meters relay.
</P>
