<HEADLINE> Chinese Communities in US West Coast to Celebrate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Thousands of local residents
of Chinese ancestry here are expected to attend a grand gathering
to celebrate Hong Kong's return to China.
</P>
<P>
Chinese community leaders from southern California told a press
conference that the gathering will take place on June 28 in
Weingart Stadium of Los Angeles Jr. College, which can hold 20,000
people.
</P>
<P>
A 32-member working committee has been set up for the
celebration, "Welcome Home Hong Kong Spectacular," featuring
parades, floral floats, dances, marching bands, symphonic music
and display of fireworks.
</P>
<P>
Similar celebrations will be held by the Chinese communities in
San Diego, San Francisco, Phoenix as well as Honolulu and cities
in the east, the committee said.
</P>
<P>
The local Chinese take a pride in the return of Hong Kong to
China from where they or their ancestors have come from because it
marks an end to the humiliations China suffered from one and a
half centuries after the Opium War, the community leaders said.
</P>
<P>
Other celebrations of smaller scale such as seminars and
evening parties will also be held and attract as well as the
majority Americans.
</P>
<P>
Some people from the U.S. west coast will go to Hong Kong to
attend the celebrations there scheduled in the evening of June 30.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
