<HEADLINE> UN's Special Envoy to Visit W. Sahara </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, April 18 (Xinhua) -- James A. Baker III, the UN
Secretary-General's personal envoy for Western Sahara, was
scheduled to start his visit to the region on April 22, a UN
spokesman announced here today.
</P>
<P>
Baker would visit Rabat, Tindouf, Algiers and Nouakchott for
consultations with the Government of Morocco, the leadership of
the POLISARIO and meetings with the governments fo the two
neighboring countries, Algeria and Mauritania, according to Juan
Carlos Brandt, associate spokesman for UN secretary-general.
</P>
<P>
Baker would make a fresh assessment of the situation and would
examine, together with the parties and the neighboring countries,
obstacles blocking the implementation of the Settlement Plan for
Western Sahara. He will report to the Secretary-General on his
findings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
