<HEADLINE> 7 British Youths Jailed for Raping Austrian Tourist </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Seven London youths were sentenced
today to 10 to 12 years imprisonment each for raping an Austrian
tourist and then trying to drown her in a canal.
</P>
<P>
"This case of rape is as horrifying and revolting as any could
be," judge Sir Lawrence Verney said before sentencing the gang
members, aged from 14 to 17.
</P>
<P>
An eighth member of the gang, the 14-year-old ring leader, will
be sentenced later after psychiatric assessment.
</P>
<P>
The youths -- four blacks, two Filipinos, a Columbian and one
who was half-English and half-Greek -- had repeatedly raped the
32-year-old woman and then thrown her into a canal in north
London's Kings Cross area even though she said she could not swim.
</P>
<P>
But she managed to escape from the other side of the canal and
later reported her case to police. 
</P>
</TEXT>
